-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/hungary-s-mkb-plans-to-sell-its-romanian-unit-financiar-reports.html
 MKB Bank, the Hungarian subsidiary
of Bayerische Landesbank, plans to sell its Romanian unit by
2013, Ziarul Financiar reported today, citing a bank report.  The Budapest-based bank may get as much as 2.4 billion
forint ($13 million) for the unprofitable unit, which is likely
to post further losses this year and next, because of bad loans,
according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
